message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Oxygen therapy in neonates can lead to retinopathy of prematurity, which can ultimately lead to blindness. Atelectasis can be a consequence of not receiving enough oxygen, rather than receiving supplemental oxygen. Anosmia and cardiac anomalies are unrelated to oxygen therapy in this context.

Atelectasis may occur due to the underlying lung pathology, but it is not a consequence of oxygen therapy. Anosmia and cardiac anomalies are not associated with oxygen therapy in neonates.
